sMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528113\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gzv1665702924419.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gzv1665702924419.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gzv1665702924419.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gzv1665702924419\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Deployment Considerations for Performance and Scalability\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"gzv1665702924419__deployment_considerations_for_performance_and_scalability_141184\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">There are a number of measures you can take to improve performance an scalability when configuring and deploying your application.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gzv1665702924419__p_d46526e1_d46527e1_d46528e1\">During deployment, you can do the following to improve performance:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gzv1665702924419__li_d23171e1_d23172e1_d23173e1\">Consider placing frequently used Uniface objects, such as UAR files, forms, and services, on the client for faster performance.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gzv1665702924419__li_d23174e1_d23175e1_d23176e1\">Balance loads over infrastructure, for example, direct heavy processing loads to high-performance servers, or dynamically direct requests to available servers.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gzv1665702924419__li_d23177e1_d23178e1_d23179e1\">Balance loads over time, deferring batch processes to off-peak hours.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gzv1665702924419__li_d23180e1_d23181e1_d23182e1\">Tune the database to use database-specific functionality. If the application has been designed or implemented to be DBMS-independent, it is possible to switch to a more powerful DBMS. However, this reduces portability and makes it more difficult to change the database.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gzv1665702924419__li_d23183e1_d23184e1_d23185e1\">Install additional computing resources, such as additional memory, higher-speed servers, or additional data storage.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gzv1665702924419__p_d46529e1_d46530e1_d46531e1\">For more information about improving performance with deployed applications, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mxg1665702923638.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mxg1665702923638.html\" title=\"Uniface runs on a wide range of platforms with different memory management characteristics, so Uniface includes its own memory management system. This enables Uniface to ignore the underlying memory management details of the operating system. However, this means that it is not always possible to optimize Uniface for a specific platform.\">Uniface Memory Use</a> , <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"prf1665702921294.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/prf1665702921294.html\" title=\"Load balancing entails distributing the application components, databases, servers, and processing to make best use of the available resources. This can affect both where application files are located and when processing takes place.\">Load Balancing</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eiv1665702924508.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eiv1665702924508.html\" title=\"The location and configuration of Uniface servers and tools can affect performance.\">Uniface Servers</a>, and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bjy1665702922231.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bjy1665702922231.html\" title=\"The DBMS is the system layer that an application must access directly. Uniface interacts with a DBMS via a DBMS-specific connector. The DBMS contributes to the system load, so it is an area of interest for performance optimization.\">Database Tuning</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528113\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528113\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Deployment Considerations for Performance and Scalability Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Deployment Considerations for Performance and Scalability There are a number of measures you can take to improve performance an scalability when configuring and deploying your application. During deployment, you can do the following to improve performance: Consider placing frequently used Uniface objects, such as UAR files, forms, and services, on the client for faster performance. Balance loads over infrastructure, for example, direct heavy processing loads to high-performance servers, or dynamically direct requests to available servers. Balance loads over time, deferring batch processes to off-peak hours. Tune the database to use database-specific functionality. If the application has been designed or implemented to be DBMS-independent, it is possible to switch to a more powerful DBMS. However, this reduces portability and makes it more difficult to change the database. Install additional computing resources, such as additional memory, higher-speed servers, or additional data storage. For more information about improving performance with deployed applications, see Uniface Memory Use , Load Balancing , Uniface Servers , and Database Tuning . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}